member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyValuationMeasures.MarketCapitalisationInMillion
member.summary: The total dollar value of all outstanding shares. Computed as shares times current market price. Capitalization is a measure of corporate size.
member.remarks: Formula: Current Market Price Per Share x Number of Shares Outstanding Intraday Value Shares outstanding is taken from the most recently filed quarterly or annual report and Market Cap is calculated using shares outstanding.

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyValuationMeasures.EnterpriseValueInMillion
member.summary: Enterprise Value is a measure of theoretical takeover price, and is useful in comparisons against income statement line items above the interest expense/income lines such as revenue and EBITDA.
member.remarks: Formula: Market Cap + Total Debt - Total Cash & Short Term Investments

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyValuationMeasures.TrailingPE
member.summary: A popular valuation ratio calculated by dividing the current market price by trailing 12-month (ttm) Earnings Per Share.
member.remarks: Formula: Current Market Price / Earnings Per Share Intraday Value Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyValuationMeasures.ForwardPE
member.summary: A valuation ratio calculated by dividing the current market price by projected 12-month Earnings Per Share.
member.remarks: Formula: Current Market Price / Projected Earnings Per Share Fiscal Year Ending

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyValuationMeasures.PEGRatio
member.summary: Forward-looking measure rather than typical earnings growth measures, which look eck in time (historical). Used to measure a stock's valuation against its projected 5-yr growth rate.
member.remarks: Formula: P/E Ratio / 5-Yr Expected EPS Growth 5 years expected

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyValuationMeasures.PriceToSales
member.summary: A valuation ratio calculated by dividing the current market price by trailing 12-month (ttm) Total Revenues. Often used to value unprofitable companies.
member.remarks: Formula: Current Market Price / Total Revenues Per Share Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyValuationMeasures.PriceToBook
member.summary: A valuation ratio calculated by dividing the current market price by the most recent quarter's (mrq) Book Value Per Share.
member.remarks: Formula: Current Market Price / Book Value Per Share Most Recent Quarter

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyValuationMeasures.EnterpriseValueToRevenue
member.summary: Firm value compared against revenue. Provides a more rigorous comparison than the Price/Sales ratio by removing the effects of capitalization from both sides of the ratio. Since revenue is unaffected by the interest income/expense line item, the appropriate value comparison should also remove the effects of capitalization, as EV does.
member.remarks: Formula: Enterprise Value / Total Revenues Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyValuationMeasures.EnterpriseValueToEBITDA
member.summary: Firm value compared against EBITDA (Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization). See Enterprise Value/Revenue.
member.remarks: Formula: Enterprise Value / EBITDA Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.FiscalYearEnds
member.summary: The date of the end of the firm's accounting year.

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.MostRecentQuarter
member.summary: Date for the most recent quarter end for which data is available on the Key Statistics page. This period is often abbreviated as "MRQ."

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.ProfitMarginPercent
member.summary: Also known as Return on Sales, this value is the Net Income After Taxes for the trailing 12 months divided by Total Revenue for the same period and is expressed as a percentage.
member.remarks: Formula: (Net Income / Total Revenues) x 100 Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.OperatingMarginPercent
member.summary: This item represents the difference between the Total Revenues and the Total Operating Costs divided by Total Revenues, and is expressed as a percentage. Total Operating Costs consist of: (a) Cost of Goods Sold (b) Total (c) Selling, General & Administrative Expenses (d) Total R & D Expenses (e) Depreciation & Amortization and (f) Total Other Operating Expenses, Total. A ratio used to measure a company's operating efficiency.
member.remarks: Formula: [(Total Revenues - Total Operating Costs) / (Total Revenues)] x 100 Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.ReturnOnAssetsPercent
member.summary: This ratio shows percentage of Returns to Total Assets of the company. This is a useful measure in analyzing how well a company uses its assets to produce earnings.
member.remarks: Formula: Earnings from Continuing Operations / Average Total Equity Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.ReturnOnEquityPercent
member.summary: This is a measure of the return on money provided by the firms' owners. This ratio represents Earnings from Continuing Operations divided by average Total Equity and is expressed as a percentage.
member.remarks: Formula: [(Earnings from Continuing Operations) / Total Common Equity] x 100 Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.RevenueInMillion
member.summary: The amount of money generated by a company's business activities. Also known as Sales.
member.remarks: Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.RevenuePerShare
member.summary: Revenue in relation to shares.
member.remarks: Formula: Total Revenues / Weighted Average Shares Outstanding Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.QuarterlyRevenueGrowthPercent
member.summary: The growth of Quarterly Total Revenues from the same quarter a year ago.
member.remarks: Formula: [(Qtrly Total Revenues x Qtrly Total Revenues (yr ago)) / Qtrly Total Revenues (yr ago)] x 100 Year Over Year

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.GrossProfitInMillion
member.summary: This item represents Total Revenues minus Cost Of Goods Sold, Total.
member.remarks: Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.EBITDAInMillion
member.summary: The accounting acronym EBITDA stands for "Earnings Before Interest, Tax, Depreciation, and Amortization."
member.remarks: Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.NetIncomeAvlToCommonInMillion
member.summary: This ratio shows percentage of Net Income to Common Excluding Extra Items less Earnings Of Discontinued Operations to Total Revenues. This is the dollar amount accruing to common shareholders for dividends and retained earnings.
member.remarks: Formula: Net Income - Preferred Dividend and Other Adjustments - Earnings Of Discontinued Operations - Extraordinary Item & Accounting Change Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.DilutedEPS
member.summary: This is the Adjusted Income Available to Common Stockholders (based on Generally Accepted Accounting Principles, GAAP) for the trailing 12 months divided by the trailing 12 month weighted average shares outstanding. Diluted EPS uses diluted weighted average shares in the calculation, or the weighted average shares assuming all convertible securities are exercised.
member.remarks: Formula: (Net Income - Preferred Dividend and Other Adjustments)/ Weighted Average Diluted Shares Outstanding Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.QuaterlyEarningsGrowthPercent
member.summary: The growth of Quarterly Net Income from the same quarter a year ago.
member.remarks: Formula: [(Qtrly Net Income x Qtrly Net Income (yr ago)) / Qtrly Net Income (yr ago)] x 100 Year Over Year

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.TotalCashInMillion
member.summary: The Total Cash and Short-term Investments on the elance sheet as of the most recent quarter.
member.remarks: Most Recent Quarter

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.TotalCashPerShare
member.summary: This is the Total Cash plus Short Term Investments divided by the Shares Outstanding at the end of the most recent fiscal quarter.
member.remarks: Most Recent Quarter

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.TotalDeptInMillion
member.summary: The Total Debt on the elance sheet as of the most recent quarter.
member.remarks: Formula: Short Term Borrowings + Current Portion of Long Term Debt + Current Portion of Capital Lease + Long Term Debt + Long Term Capital Lease + Finance Division Debt Current + Finance Division Debt Non Current Most Recent Quarter

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.TotalDeptPerEquity
member.summary: This ratio is Total Debt for the most recent fiscal quarter divided by Total Shareholder Equity for the same period.
member.remarks: Formula: [(Long-term Debt + Capital Leases + Finance Division Debt Non-Current + Short-term Borrowings + Current Portion of Long-term Debt + Current Portion of Capital Lease Obligation + Finance Division Debt Current) / (Total Common Equity + Total Preferred Equity)] x 100 Most Recent Quarter

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.CurrentRatio
member.summary: This is the ratio of Total Current Assets for the most recent quarter divided by Total Current Liabilities for the same period.
member.remarks: Formula: Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities Most Recent Quarter

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.BookValuePerShare
member.summary: This is defined as the Common Shareholder's Equity divided by the Shares Outstanding at the end of the most recent fiscal quarter.
member.remarks: Formula: Total Common Equity / Total Common Shares Outstanding Most Recent Quarter

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.OperatingCashFlowInMillion
member.summary: Net cash used or generated in operating activities during the stated period of time. It reflects net impact of all operating activity transactions on the cash flow of the entity. This GAAP figure is taken directly from the company's Cash Flow Statement and might include significant non-recurring items.
member.remarks: Formula: Net Income + Depreciation and Amortization, Total + Other Amortization + Other Non-Cash Items, Total + Change in Working Capital Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyFinancialHighlights.LeveredFreeCashFlowInMillion
member.summary: This figure is a normalized item that excludes non-recurring items and also takes into consideration cash inflows from financing activities such as debt or preferred stock issuances.
member.remarks: Formula: (EBIT + Interest Expense) x (1 x Tax Rate) + Depreciation & Amort., Total + Other Amortization + Capital Expenditure + Sale (Purchase) of Intangible assets - Change in Net Working Capital + Pref. Dividends Paid + Total Debt Repaid + Total Debt Issued + Repurchase of Preferred + Issuance of Preferred Stock -- [Where: Tax Rate = 0.375] Trailing Twelve Months

member.name: P:MaasOne.Finance.YahooFinance.CompanyTradingInfo.Beta
member.summary: The Beta used is Beta of Equity. Beta is the monthly price change of a particular company relative to the monthly price change of the S&P500. The time period for Beta is 3 years (36 months) when available.
